-- PRESS DIGEST-Hong Kong - Jan 27 
-- By Yimou Lee
-- Sun Jan 26, 2014 09:11PM EST
-- None



HONG KONG, Jan 27 (Reuters) - These are some of the leading stories in Hong Kong newspapers on Monday. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

SOUTH CHINA MORNING POST  -- Almost 100 companies have warned of either losing money or recording significant declines in profitability for the last year, filings with Hong Kong Exchanges and Clearing since November last year show. The reporting season starts next month and ends on March 31. (http://link.reuters.com/vaz36v) -- Foreign funds have ramped up their exposure to Shanghai's manufacturing sector, despite a freshly minted free-trade zone that is intended to be the springboard for efforts to intensify focus on financial services. (http://link.reuters.com/zaz36v)  THE STANDARD -- Electronic checks, available from the second half of next year, could boost the competitiveness of Hong Kong, Financial Secretary John Tsang Chun-wah said. (http://link.reuters.com/bez36v) -- K Wah International Holdings <0173.HK> spent 115 million yuan ($19 million) on a 13,686 square-metre plot in Dongguan, while Swire Properties <1972.HK> said it will jointly develop a residential-cum-retail project in the core business area of Dalian city with CITIC Real Estate and Dalian Port Real Estate. (http://link.reuters.com/huz36v) -- The local home market turned quiet on the weekend before the Lunar New Year with only five homes sold at the 10 major estates tracked by Centaline Property Agency. (http://link.reuters.com/cez36v)  HONG KONG ECONOMIC JOURNAL  -- Hong Kong recorded only 13 new home transactions over the weekend, a 90 percent drop from a week earlier and the lowest in seven months.  ORIENTAL DAILY NEWS  -- Property developer CIFI Holdings Group Co Ltd's <0884.HK> chairman said the company set its sales target for 2014 at 22 billion yuan, a 40 percent increase from a year earlier.  SINGTAO DAILY -- Hong Kong Exchanges and Clearing Ltd (HKEx) <0388.HK> is studying plans to tighten rules for shell listing and reverse mergers, according to sources.  WEN WEI PO -- Longfor Properties Co Ltd <0960.HK> spent 4.2 billion yuan on a 128,383 sq.m. plot in Hangzhou for residential, commercial and office use, while China SCE Property Holdings Ltd won two land slots in Quanzhou for residential and commercial use for 800 million yuan.   -- CITIC Securities Co Ltd <6030.HK> said it won a bid for land use rights for a property project in Shenzhen for 3.6 billion yuan to build the company's headquarters.